  Privacy Act Officer : Business Actor

The Privacy Act requires agencies to have at least one person who fulfils the role of a privacy officer. A privacy officer must be familiar with the privacy principles in the Privacy Act, work to make sure the agency complies with the Privacy Act, deal with any complaints from the agency's clients about possible breaches of privacy, deal with requests for access to personal information, or correction of personal information, and act as the agency’s liaison.

  Determine Competitive Range : Business Role

This is a required step for FAR Part 15 negotiated acquisitions. COR makes a recommendation for competitive range based on technical evaluation scores. CO makes a competitive range determination document, and notifying vendors not in the competitive range

  SAM.gov : Business Actor

Vendor must register to be eligible for a Contract. CO uses this website to confirm that all representations and certifications are updated and that they do not appear on the excluded parties list. https://www.SAM.gov/SAM/

 

 

Look up to verify that vendors are registered in SAM and have an active registration. Also to verify that vendors are not on the excluded parties list. Post-Award and Contract Administration: CO verifies vendor information in SAM that the vendor has not been added to the excluded parties list, and that they have an active registration

  US Department of Labor National Pre-award Registry : Business Actor

Website for EEO clearance pre-Award. CO/CSs review to confirm successful awardee is on the compliance list. If they are not, then CO/CS is required to contact regional POC for approval prior to Award. https://ofccp.dol-ESA.gov/preaward/PA_reg.html

  Wage Determinations Online.gov : Business Actor

Location for Federal Contracting Officers to use to obtain appropriate Service Contract Act wage determinations for each official Contract action. https://www.wdol.gov/
